<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-71-0562 </DOCNO><TEXT>The viability of the uranium industry in the United States is discussedagainst the background of past and present government responsibilitiesin this area and pending legislation. The history of the uranium industryis outlined. Federal responsibilities over the industry are illustrated.Criteria for the viability of the US domestic uranium industry are listed.The three pieces of proposed legislation before the Congress are explained.The first is a resolution disapproving of the proposed enrichment servicessubmitted by the Department of Energy in 1986. The second concerns tradesanctions against South Africa and the third concerns tailings reclamationand restrictions on imported uranium. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>